=== Irregular Verbs? ===
The same rule is used for all of the Turkish verbs. There are no irregular verbs as in English. 

{{Turkish/TOC}}

Future tense is used to express future in Turkish. Turkish future tense is the equivalent of ''be going to'' and ''will''. 

=== Affirmative - Olumlu ===
The suffixes -ecek or -acak (according to the vowel harmony) and the personal ending are added to the verb stem. The "k" in the suffixes become a "ğ" before the 1st personal endings:
{{Turkish/Box||{{turkish/c|Verb stem}} (+ buffer letter {{tr/suff|y}} if the verb is ending in a vowel) + appropriate form of {{turkish/Suffix|ecek|dash=no}} + {{turkish/c|personal ending}}}}
{| width="100%"
|width=50%|
<!--Table 1-->
{| {{Turkish/Table|width=100%|verb inflection • [[Turkish/Future Tense|future tense]] |{{tr/word|gel|to come}}|columns=4}}

! {{tr/word|ben|color=purple}} {{tr/word|gel|come}}{{tr/suff|eceğ|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff|im|color=purple|dash=no}}
| I will come
! {{tr/word|biz|color=purple}} {{tr/word|gel|come}}{{tr/suff|eceğ|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff|iz|color=purple|dash=no}}
| we will come
|-
! {{tr/word|sen|color=purple}} {{tr/word|gel|come}}{{tr/suff|ecek|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff|sin|color=purple|dash=no}}
| you will come
! {{tr/word|siz|color=purple}} {{tr/word|gel|come}}{{tr/suff|ecek|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff|siniz|color=purple|dash=no}}
| you will come
|-
! {{tr/word|o|color=purple}} {{tr/word|gel|come}}{{tr/suff|ecek|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff||color=purple|dash=no}}
| he/she/it will come
! {{tr/word|onlar|color=purple}} {{tr/word|gel|come}}{{tr/suff|ecek|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff|ler|color=purple|dash=no}}
| they will come
|}
|width="50%"|
{| {{Turkish/Table|width=100%|verb inflection • [[Turkish/Future Tense|future tense]] |{{tr/word|koş|to run}}|columns=4}}

! {{tr/word|ben|color=purple}} {{tr/word|koş|run}}{{tr/suff|acağ|color=b|dash=no}}{{tr/suff|ım|color=purple|dash=no}}
| I will run
